    {
      "id": "faq-1",
      "type": "paragraph.faq_item",
      "values": {
        "question": "How long does it take to get started with Verdant?",
        "answer": "<p>Most customers are up and running within 2 weeks. Our onboarding team helps you connect your data sources, configure your emission factors, and generate your first carbon footprint report. For enterprise deployments with custom integrations, plan for 4-6 weeks.</p>"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "faq-2",
      "type": "paragraph.faq_item",
      "values": {
        "question": "What data sources does Verdant integrate with?",
        "answer": "<p>We integrate with 200+ enterprise systems including SAP, Oracle, Salesforce, Workday, and QuickBooks. We also support custom APIs, CSV uploads, and IoT sensor data. Our data team can build custom connectors for proprietary systems.</p>"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "faq-3",
      "type": "paragraph.faq_item",
      "values": {
        "question": "Is Verdant compliant with international reporting standards?",
        "answer": "<p>Yes. Verdant supports GHG Protocol, CSRD, SEC climate disclosure rules, TCFD, CDP, SBTi, and ISO 14064. Our reports are designed to be audit-ready and have been validated by all Big Four accounting firms.</p>"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "faq-4",
      "type": "paragraph.faq_item",
      "values": {
        "question": "How does the AI emissions estimation work?",
        "answer": "<p>Our AI models are trained on millions of verified emissions data points across industries. When primary data isn't available (especially for Scope 3), our models estimate emissions using industry-specific factors, spend data, and supply chain intelligence. We're transparent about data quality scores so you know where to prioritize primary data collection.</p>"
      }
